caption: Gets busy on the weekends, but only adds to the atmosphere. The guacamole is life changing. Seriously.

The service was friendly and very fast. The food was fresh tasting and good portion sizes too. The owner also seemed very attentive and gave us a sample of new menu items. Highly recommend dining at this great local restaurant!!
I love EVERYTHING on the menu!! Can't wait to have some Midday Margs!!
Great food and friendly staff. Place was very clean. We will be back.
The food here is always solid Amer-Mex and the Crane Masada is excellent...their marinade and preparation is exquisite. Service has really tightened up. Belly was excellent..

(Translated by Google) Special tacos, this is how the restaurant announces them and they are not wrong, the flank steak tacos are delicious and accompanied with a guacamole that is truly a delicacy.  (Original) Tacos especiales, así los anuncia el restaurante y no se equivocan los tacos de arrachera son buenísimos y acompañados con un guacamole que es verdaderamente un manjar.
Great 🌮
Huge servings. The burrito and tacos are saucy. Be sure to grab a napkin. Also they have a cute dog mascot. They wrap it in paper and aluminum to keep it warm.

Easily 5 stars! I had couple tacos, French fries, and a bite of a burrito. Everything was outstanding. The tacos were soaked in sauce but so damn tasty. Portions are really massive for the price!  Big thumbs up for very up to date and easy to use online ordering system.

I love the place! The food was delicious. I ordered three meals and all of us were very satisfied with the taste. The chips and queso were crunchy and fresh. I had the steak burrito “lulu style” and it was very tasty- especially with added salsa too! This was during my lunch time at noon & the staff were very quick and friendly! I would definitely recommend this place. 👍
Eggs are real

Ordered a steak burrito, nasty! Meat was tasteless and the amount of meat for the price was ridiculous. Was told it was a 14" burrito but came out to be 7". The disclaimer was that the tortilla wad 14". Paid 12.27 for a tasteless bland burrito. Not worth it at all.
Good fast food wachamole was bad however
Tried a Chicken Burrito today. The place appeared clean , service was good but the burrito got 2 thums down. Never had a worse burrito.
Tacos are good a lil pricey though definitely will try again
Horrible food, services was nice though
Great steak tacos, fast and fresh. Managers are on site and there to help.
Taco tastes really good. Like the spicy sauce!
Great local taco place. Owner is a great guy.

Had a steak burrito today and it was delicious and straight to the point. They have great taste and great prices so I will be back for sure.  After our meal, a guy with his dog walked up to us and asked how the food was and I told him that it was amazing and that he should try it. The guy ended up being the owner and that Taco Lulu was named after his dog!
Best tacos Downtown !! Tacos de al Pastor with salsa verde are the bestttt!!!
Great food, good service!
Very tasty and fresh
The steak tacos are beyond amazing. Also, recommend the chicken and pork tamales as well as the queso! The vibe in the back is super cool as well!
Al Pastor and Steak burritos are both delicious

I order from them a lot at work and they’re so good. I usually get a guacamole platillo and the portions are great. Their chips are nice and crunchy, and I love that the beans are vegetarian friendly.
Hours listed on google are wrong...not open on sundays.
Food gets to you quickly after you order.  The chicken tacos are really good.  I had also had a taco salad and nachos.
I moved to the loop 10 months ago, Taco Lulu is the best thing ever happened in this neighborhood so far! The food is soooo good, local, and the people are so friendly.
The 🐔 tacos are delish. Actually, so are the pork Al pastor. I liked the steak tacos too but the meat can be chewy. Good service and solid Mexican establishment. I'd recommend it to my friends.
Awesome food and staff. Dined-in, then ordered different items to take-home. Highly recommended!!
The steak tacos are the best tacos I have ever tasted so delicious!

Taco Lulu is the Mexican cuisine restaurant that has won my heart. The owner is a kind person who received me, my family and a great friend, with much affection and enthusiasm. He provided us with a delicious, balanced and well prepared meal. Each bite was a party full of incredible flavors in my mouth. Thanks for the experience and I hope to visit the restaurant on a next visit to Chicago.
Best taco's in Chicago!!!
The food is incredible and the service is great! The owner is hands down the nicest guy you’ll ever meet (and loves his cute girl lulu, check out the picture by the registers).

(Translated by Google) Super awesome atmosphere and tasty food. It’s by far a must-visiting place. Unmissable.  Wonderful food with a burst of flavors never seen. Hands down the best chicken taco salad I've ever had. Meat is seasoned very well and full of flavor. Staff is very friendly and restaurant is clean. Will definitely be back to try other items on the menu... thanks for side meat sampler. It was delicious!

We come here all the time. The food is delicious, owner and staff are amazing friendly people. The place is dog friendly which is a plus on the cold days when we're walking the dog and picking up food, I can bring him in. They're always trying new recipes and it's ALWAYS delicious. Fresh and fast all the time and service with conversation and a smile. You won't be disappointed! 🤤
Steak tacos and steak nachos were fantastic. Michael was extremely nice and helpful. Will definitely be returning.
Great tacos and salsa.
Excellent food and friendly quick service, juicy and tender steak, their steak tacos will have your mouth watering!!!

I love Mexican food but this place is just not very good. Went on a Saturday afternoon and was one of two tables of customers. Was kind of put off when I walked in I heard the server say he would have brought the food to her the other customers table. When my food came he shouts my number, I wait he shouts, I wait he shouts my number again so I go pickup the order from the counter, I guess he would only deliver the other customers food  Again 1 of 2 tables mind you. The queso was tasteless. I had a steak, pastor and ground beef taco. The meat was extremely low quality and I could not tell the difference between the pastor and ground beef, lol. The steak was way overcooked, dryest steak I ever had. My wife had the taco salad with chicken and that wasn't bad, just not a whole lot of flavor. The best thing about the place was the salsa, that was very good.  Take a look at all the 4-5 star reviews of this place, look at how many other reviews those people have written. Now look at all the bad reviews, look to see how many other reviews those people have left. Don't be fooled, this place won't last a year. The high stars are the friends and family reviewers
Fast service, great chicken tacos
I’ve visited here many times for lunch.  The food is fantastic and the staff is very friendly and helpful.  To go or takeout is quick and I’d recommend the steak tacos or steak taco salad!
good tacos at a reasonable price - the pork is more like chorizo than carnitas which is not a bad thing, just something to note when you visit.
Fresh ingredients make the tacos perfect. Kind service and a clean atmosphere.
Have ordered from here twice, just had first dine-in. This is the best Mexican food to happen to the area in quite some time, and has quickly become our go-to.
Really enjoy and love coming here, great staff and owner/great food... I eat lunch here M-F 😁
Love this place. Perfect quick lunch spot.
Best tacos in the area, fast and friendly service, and big portions.
Best tacos in river north
Great Mexican food!
Good Mexican food. Quick service.

Came into this place looking for a good burrito so i took 2 to go i noticed the meat wasnt cooked upon order it was already pre made which should of been a red flag after eating them a few hours later bubble guts started..... and you guys know what happened next totally dissapointed
Food was good but pricey.  2 steak tacos, chips and a drink was almost $14.
Great Mexican restaurant and great prices
Fast  and friendly service, reasonably priced, and some of the best food I've had in a long time. Will definitely be back regularly.
Fine food, mediocre, but tasted okay. Over charged me, and gave me the wrong thing they over charged me for. Fine if you just want some quick, okay, tacos downtown.

Nice look inside.had a steak and pork taco which I enjoyed .no complaints.beans were very good.rice was very good, not dry.the person I was with had a steak taco .she said it was good.fast service.the cashier was very pleasant.was clean. Inside . will be back.the salsas were good.I drove a parts van all over chicagoland for many years.been to numerous Mexican restaurants.this one is worth the stop.
Today was my first time at taco lulu. A lot of my Amtrak friends said it was good. I had to try it for myself.  The tacos, chips and guac was great. I give it a 5....
Food is delicious & the employees r friendly
The chicken tacos are fantastic!
Tasty, friendly and byob!
Great quality food, quick friendly service, cute restaurant!

Good tasting tacos and they definitely load the tacos up with meat. It's also the establishment I have found in the loop area that's BYOB as well. Even during peak hours, the service was good and fast.

Overpriced for poor quality food. Was highly disappointed when my food arrived. I also didn't get the soda I paid for. Would not recommend Taco Lulu. This is not authentic mexican food and the staff simply doesn't care to make anything right.
Varying quality from visit to visit, house made chorizo was way off. Ingredient quality needs to go up to better reflect pricing.
Best Tacos and Great Staff! Very posh place and clean
Steak tacos were not bad. Al pastor was very dry and had lack of seasoning.

Went there for lunch and got the pastor burrito. The quality of meat and ingredients is simply bad. The pastor is certainly not authentic Mexican. It's basically some low grade ground pork with some spices thrown on top. I usually love burritos and I didn't even eat the whole thing. The only redeeming quality was that they gave you a large quantity of food for a below average price. I guess you get what you pay for.
Burritos are huge! My personal favorite is the chorizo burrito! So tasty and authentic Mexican food. Love this place.
Vegan and vegetarian friendly...great service

Tacos were easily 4 stars, but the owner walked around with the restaurant's namesake Lulu,  insisting on introducing her to all. She (Lulu) was dangled above everybody's table, while the owner introduced (and scratched) her. To everybody.  Don't get me wrong, I'm a huge dog lover, but there's something terribly wrong with scratching/petting your dog over a table of people eating tacos. People with allergies, Non-dog lovers, or just general people wanting to eat without dogs over your food,may want to be cautious. Where is this dog being kept in the restaurant? Why over my food? So many questions...
Ordered 2 steak tacos and a side of rice for 12 dollars. Tacos were pretty dry and side of rice was so small.

First time having food from Taco Lulu.  Chicken was not  grilled, more like shredded, but very yummy.  Skirt steak was very tasty.  I noticed the tortillas were a little cold, but didn't bother me.  Saw someone get the steak nachos, plate was filled with meat.  I'll definitely go back.  12:00pm - 12:30pm gets extremely busy.

The veggie tacos are a joke. There is no rice and beans substance on them. Literally just toppings that would go on a taco with meat without any other substance. Avocado or guac is not a choice of substance. The guac had hardly and avocado in it it was more tomato and onions than avocado. I wouldn't consider this place good for a vegetarian. Go to the taco truck on Franklin for better veggie tacos with actual seasonal veggies, rice and beans in them for substance.
Ok Steak, a smoother ordering and preparation process is needed.
Nachos were Great ! Out of this world. Tacos were DRY. Refine the cooking time. Also ...everyone wore gloves but not head cover like hats.
you should use the smaller flour tortillas instead of the giant el milagro ones for your tacos, also heat it up more it got cold real quick.  The tortilla needs more heat too.
Love it
